34A-303. Liability of members and managers. (a) Except as otherwise provided in subsection (c), the debts, obligations, and liabilities A debt, obligation, or other liability of a limited liability company, whether arising in contract, tort, or otherwise, are is solely the debts, obligations, and liabilities debt, obligation, or other liability of the company. A member or manager is not personally liable, directly or indirectly, by way of contribution or otherwise, for a debt, obligation, or liability of the company solely by reason of being or acting as a member or manager. This subsection applies regardless of the dissolution of the company. (b) The failure of a limited liability company to observe the usual company formalities or requirements relating to the exercise of its company powers or management of its business activities and affairs is not a ground for imposing personal liability on the members or managers a member or manager for liabilities a debt, obligation, or other liability of the company. (c) All or specified members of a limited liability company are liable in their capacity as members for all or specified debts, obligations, or liabilities of the company if: (1) A provision to that effect is contained in the articles of organization; and (2) A member so liable has consented in writing to the adoption of the provision or to be bound by the provision."}, {"bill_id": 11601, "bill_version_id": 68857, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "2020-02-26T16:52:38.577-06:00", "bill_text": "ENTITLED An Act to revise the Uniform Limited Liability Company Act. Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of South Dakota: Section 1. That \u00a7 47-34A-303 be AMENDED: 47-34A-303. Liability of members and managers. (a) A debt, obligation, or other liability of a limited liability company is solely the debt, obligation, or other liability of the company. A member or manager is not personally liable, directly or indirectly, by way of contribution or otherwise, for a debt, obligation, or liability of the company solely by reason of being or acting as a member or manager. This subsection applies regardless of the dissolution of the company. (b) The failure of a limited liability company to observe formalities relating to the exercise of its powers or management of its activities and affairs is not a ground for imposing liability on a member or manager for a debt, obligation, or other liability of the company. An Act to revise the Uniform Limited Liability Company Act. I certify that the attached Act originated in the: House as Bill No. 1109 Chief Clerk Speaker of the House Attest: Chief Clerk President of the Senate Attest: Secretary of the Senate House Bill No. 1109 File No. ____ Chapter No. ______ Received at this Executive Office this _____ day of _____________, 2020 at ____________M. By for the Governor The attached Act is hereby approved this ________ day of ______________, A.D., 2020 Governor STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA, ss. Office of the Secretary of State Filed ____________, 2020 at _________ o'clock __M. Secretary of State By Asst. Secretary of State"}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 11601, "action_date": "2020-01-28T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 64105, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/64105.pdf", "status_text": "First read in House and referred to", "journal_page": 75, "committee_id_action": 480, "committee_id_assigned": 448, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 11601, "action_date": "2020-02-12T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 67334, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/67334.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for hearing", "journal_page": null, "committee_id_action": 448, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 11601, "action_date": "2020-02-12T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 67335, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/67335.pdf", "status_text": "Do Pass", "journ